== Pickled Veggies ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim, halve, and thinly slice @radishes{3}; halve @demi-baguette{2}
lengthwise. Halve @Super Select cucumber{1} lengthwise and thinly slice
on a diagonal into half-moons. Quarter @lime{1}.

Place @shredded carrots{4%oz} and radishes in a medium #microwave-safe
bowl{}; toss with @ponzu sauce{6%ml}, half the @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}
(you'll use the rest later), @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Microwave on high for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside, stirring occasionally,
until ready to serve.

== Pulled Pork ==

Tear @pulled pork{8%oz} into smaller pieces if necessary.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add pork and @garlic powder{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
remaining vinegar, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

While pork cooks, toast baguettes using a #toaster{} or #oven{}.

To bowl with carrot mixture, add cucumber and a squeeze of lime juice
(from half the lime); toss to coat. Taste and season generously with
salt and pepper.

Spread cut sides of top buns with @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Fill buns with
pork mixture and as many veggies as you like.

Serve with remaining veggies and remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Tonight's dinner features a favorite Vietnamese sandwich with a twist:
> pickled veggies are piled between toasty baguettes for a banh mi-inspired
> sammie, BBQ-style! Pulled pork is coated in tangy hoisin for a
> barbecue-like kick, then topped with cucumber, radishes, carrots, and
> a generous swipe of mayo.